BLUETONGUE - EUROPE (30): CYPRUS, BOVINE, SEROTYPE PENDING, OIE
***************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 5 Dec 2014
Source: OIE, WAHID weekly disease information 2014; 27(50) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=16699


Bluetongue, Cyprus
---------------------
Information received on [and dated] 5 Dec 2014 from Andreas Papaefstathiou, Acting Director, Veterinary Services, Ministry of Agriculture, Natural Resources and Environment, Nicosia, Cyprus

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 4 Dec 2014
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 4 Dec 2014
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 7 Nov 2011
Manifestation of disease: sub-clinical disease
Causal agent: Bluetongue virus
Serotype: Pending
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (basic), laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks: Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Aglantzia, Lefkosia
Date of start of the outbreak: 4 Dec 2014
Outbreak status: resolved (4 Dec 2014)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 111 / 6 / 0 / 0 / 0

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Sheep / 5.41 / 0 / 0 / 0
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: vectors

Epidemiological comment: The holding is included in the monthly surveillance programme for bluetongue. On 4 Dec 2014, 6 out of the 9 sentinel cattle reacted positively to bluetongue virus by c-ELISA, and on 5 Dec 2014, 4 cattle reacted positively by real-time PCR. Samples will be sent to the EU Reference Laboratory for virus confirmation and typing. Following the laboratory results, movements from and to the holding were prohibited, and clinical examination was carried out to investigate whether bluetongue signs were present. During the clinical examination, no animals showed any signs.

Control measures
Measures applied: quarantine; disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s); vaccination prohibited; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied; no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Animal Health Laboratory (national laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result:
Cattle / competitive ELISA (c-ELISA) / 4 Dec 2014 / Positive
Cattle / real-time PCR / 5 Dec 2014 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

The location of this outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Previously, bluetongue (BT) serotype 4 and serotype 16 have been reported in Cyprus http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Diseaseinformation/statusdetail (Note: to view the information on BT in Cyprus, choose the country, scroll down to the name of the disease (terrestrial), and choose time period). However, given the current BT situation in the area, this event could be due to BT-4.

A map of Cyprus is available at http://www.ephotopix.com/image/europe/cyprus_political_map.gif. - Mod.CRD

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3013702,82.]
